Police have killed five suspects during a shootout following an Cash-in-transit heist, in Dawn Park near Springs, this morning. Two others have been arrested. Police Minister Bheki Cele is at the scene. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - A police reservist has been arrested for his alleged role in a cash heist in Dawn Park. Five suspected robbers were subsequently killed in a shootout with police while two others were arrested. Robbers held up security guards and stole an undisclosed amount of money on Wednesday morning. READ: Five suspected CIT robbers shot dead in Boksburg They then fled to a safe house in Dawn Park, which allegedly belongs to the police officer. Police followed a tip-off and a shoot-out ensued outside the house. Some of the money has since been recovered. Police have confiscated four unlicensed firearms with ammunition.